descript.abstract: A polygon theme containing "land type" classifications based on: - dominant soil series - dominant woody plant species - hillslope units - landform characteristics (relief, soil, slope length, stream frequency) for management planning and ecological studies in the Kruger National Park.
descript.purpose: For the KNP Scientific Services GIS database - for research and cartographic products. This database is intended to be extended or incorporated into a future KNP "Regional GIS" node of SANP.
descript.supplinf: It is ESSENTIAL to use the appropriate related Look-Up Tables (LUT's) in order to interpret the Land Types. These LUT's are: landtype_general_lut.dbf; landtype_morphometry_lut.dbf; landtype_soils_kiker_lut.dbf; landtype_soils_lut.dbf. is also a table for converting old codes to the new codes: the only difference between the old new codes is that those with single digits are preceded by a "0" in the new codes; hence "LE7" becomes "LE07", for example. Venter works for SANParks in the Kruger NP under the Environmental Management Unit as Manager: Aquatic Systems is based at Phalaborwa. E-mail: freekv@parks-sa.co.za
